== Organisation ==
The EACPT is led by an Executive Committee<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eacpt.org/?q=node/9 |title=Executive Committee Members &#124; European Association for Clinical Pharmacology and Therapeutics |publisher=Eacpt.org |date= |accessdate=2012-05-13}}</ref> formed from a council of delegates from affiliated national societies<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eacpt.org/?q=node/27 |title=Members &#124; European Association for Clinical Pharmacology and Therapeutics |publisher=Eacpt.org |date= |accessdate=2012-05-13}}</ref> for clinical pharmacology and [[therapeutics]]. The executive committee officers from the 2011 biennial congress in Budapest are: Gonzalo Calvo Rojas (Spain, chairman), Tabassome Simon (France, vice-chairman), [[Donald Singer]] (United Kingdom, secretary), and Kari Kivisto (Finland, treasurer).

